Sentencas: The microfabrication of Foturan (R) glass ceramic as a potential substrate material for micro-solid oxide fuel cells (micro-SOFC) was investigated.
Titulo: Processing of Foturan® glass ceramic substrates for micro-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Foturan (R) was etched in 10% aqueous hydrofluoric (HF) acid solution at 25 degrees C with a linear rate of 22 +/- 1.7 mu m/min to create structures with an aspect ratio of 1:1 in 500 mu m-thick Foturan (R) substrates for micro-SOFCs.
Titulo: Processing of Foturan® glass ceramic substrates for micro-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The concentration of the HF etchant was found to influence the etching rate, whereas the UV-exposure time creating nuclei in the glass for subsequent crystallization of the amorphous Foturan (R) material had no significant influence on the etching rates.
Titulo: Processing of Foturan® glass ceramic substrates for micro-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The surface roughness of the crystallized Foturan (R) was determined by the crystallite size in the order of 10-15 mu m. Free-standing micro-SOFC membranes consisting of a thin film Pt cathode, an yttria-stabilized-zirconia electrolyte and a Pt anode were released by HF etching of the Foturan (R) substrate.
Titulo: Processing of Foturan® glass ceramic substrates for micro-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An open-circuit voltage of 0.57 V and a maximum power density of 209 mW/cm(2) at 550 degrees C were achieved.
Titulo: Processing of Foturan® glass ceramic substrates for micro-solid oxide fuel cells
